    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not convinced that we should use <code>abbrev</code> for new definitions instead of building API, otherwise LGTM.</p>",
        "id": 412267276,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1704946201
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"214703\">Yury G. Kudryashov</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/144837-PR-reviews/topic/.239267.20local.20graph.20operations/near/412267276\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm not convinced that we should use <code>abbrev</code> for new definitions instead of building API, otherwise LGTM.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So you want me to use <code>def</code> and not <code>abbrev</code> for <code>replaceVertex/addEdge</code>?</p>",
        "id": 412267807,
        "sender_full_name": "Jeremy Tan",
        "timestamp": 1704946531
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Let me ask <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"310045\">@Eric Wieser</span> and <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"240862\">@Oliver Nash</span> who reviewed <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6808\">#6808</a> for opinion.</p>",
        "id": 412267935,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1704946614
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think that we should use <code>def</code> unless we want to unfold the definition <em>every time</em> we call <code>simp</code>.</p>",
        "id": 412267977,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1704946657
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>While this make sense for some 1-line definitions like <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SimpleGraph.IsClique#src\">src#SimpleGraph.IsClique</a>, it's not obvious that you want to unfold the <code>Adj</code> projection of, say, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SimpleGraph.replaceVertex#doc\">docs#SimpleGraph.replaceVertex</a> every time.</p>",
        "id": 412268112,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1704946776
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"214703\">Yury G. Kudryashov</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/144837-PR-reviews/topic/.239267.20local.20graph.20operations/near/412267935\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm not convinced that we should use abbrev for new definitions instead of building API, otherwise LGTM.</p>\n<p>Let me ask Eric Wieser and Oliver Nash who reviewed <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6808\">#6808</a> for opinion.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Looking just at <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/9267\">#9267</a> I definitely agree: <code>addEdge</code> should be a <code>def</code>. Moreover the same applies to <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SimpleGraph.replaceVertex#doc\">docs#SimpleGraph.replaceVertex</a> (I missed this when reviewing <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6808\">#6808</a>).</p>",
        "id": 412298048,
        "sender_full_name": "Oliver Nash",
        "timestamp": 1704964381
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"240862\">Oliver Nash</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/144837-PR-reviews/topic/.239267.20local.20graph.20operations/near/412298048\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Looking just at <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/9267\">#9267</a> I definitely agree: <code>addEdge</code> should be a <code>def</code>. Moreover the same applies to <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SimpleGraph.replaceVertex#doc\">docs#SimpleGraph.replaceVertex</a> (I missed this when reviewing <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6808\">#6808</a>).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Done.</p>",
